## Section II: Reading Comprehension (阅读理解)

### Part A

#### Text 1 (儿童编程教育)
*It's true that high-school coding classes aren't essential for learning computer science in college...*

**21. Cortina holds that early exposure to computer science makes it easier to _______.**
- [ ] A. complete future job training
- [ ] B. remodel the way of thinking
- [ ] C. formulate logical hypotheses
- [ ] D. perfect artwork production

<details>
<summary>✅ 点击查看答案与解析</summary>

**答案：B**
**解析：** 细节题。根据题干定位到第二段，Cortina认为早期接触有益，因为对孩子来说 "transform their thought processes"（转变思维过程）比大孩子更容易。[B] remodel the way of thinking 是同义替换。
</details>

**22. In delivering lessons for high-schoolers, Flatiron has considered their _______.**
- [ ] A. experience
- [ ] B. interest
- [ ] C. career prospects
- [ ] D. academic backgrounds

<details>
<summary>✅ 点击查看答案与解析</summary>

**答案：B**
**解析：** 细节题。定位到第三段，Flatiron School的导师提到 "we try to gear lessons toward things they're interested in"（我们试图根据他们的兴趣调整课程），故选 [B] interest。
</details>

**23. Deborah Seehorn believes that the skills learned at Flatiron will _______.**
- [ ] A. help students learn other computer languages
- [ ] B. have to be upgraded when new technologies come
- [ ] C. need improving when students look for jobs
- [ ] D. enable students to make big quick money

<details>
<summary>✅ 点击查看答案与解析</summary>

**答案：A**
**解析：** 细节题。定位到第五段，Deborah指出他们学到的技能（逻辑思维和结果组织）可以 "apply to any coding language"（应用于任何编程语言），即帮助学习其他语言。
</details>

**24. According to the last paragraph, Flatiron students are expected to _______.**
- [ ] A. bring forth innovative computer technologies
- [ ] B. stay longer in the information technology industry
- [ ] C. become better prepared for the digitalized world
- [ ] D. compete with a future army of programmers

<details>
<summary>✅ 点击查看答案与解析</summary>

**答案：C**
**解析：** 推理题。最后一段提到这些学生一生都将 "surrounded by computers"，越早学会如何与机器协作越好。这表明目的是让他们为数字化世界做好准备，而非全都成为程序员。
</details>

**25. The word "coax" (Line 4, Para. 6) is closest in meaning to _______.**
- [ ] A. persuade
- [ ] B. frighten
- [ ] C. misguide
- [ ] D. challenge

<details>
<summary>✅ 点击查看答案与解析</summary>

**答案：A**
**解析：** 词义题。上下文是 "how to coax the machine into producing what they want"，意为引导或劝说机器生产想要的东西。[A] persuade (劝诱) 最符合语境。
</details>

