#### Text 2 (草原鸡保护争议)
*Biologists estimate that as many as 2 million lesser prairie chickens...*

**26. The major reason for listing the lesser prairie chicken as threatened is _______.**
- [ ] A. its drastically decreased population
- [ ] B. the underestimate of the grassland acreage
- [ ] C. a desperate appeal from some biologists
- [ ] D. the insistence of private landowners

<details>
<summary>✅ 点击查看答案与解析</summary>

**答案：A**
**解析：** 细节题。第一段提到数量从200万锐减到2.2万，第二段首句明确指出 "The crash was a major reason..."（这种暴跌是主要原因），对应 [A] drastically decreased population。
</details>

**27. The "threatened" tag disappointed some environmentalists in that it _______.**
- [ ] A. was a give-in to governmental pressure
- [ ] B. would involve fewer agencies in action
- [ ] C. granted less federal regulatory power
- [ ] D. went against conservation policies

<details>
<summary>✅ 点击查看答案与解析</summary>

**答案：C** (注：根据原文解析，此处选C更精准，指联邦监管权力变小，虽然D也有干扰性，但原文明确对比了 "endangered" 给予官员更大的监管权力 "greater regulatory power"，反之 "threatened" 则权力较小)。
**修正解析：** 第二段提到环保人士希望定为 "endangered" 因为那会给联邦官员 "greater regulatory power"，而定为 "threatened" 则意味着灵活性更大但监管权力相对较小。因此失望的原因是 [C] granted less federal regulatory power。
</details>

**28. It can be learned from Paragraph 3 that unintentional harm-doers will not be prosecuted if they _______.**
- [ ] A. agree to pay a sum for compensation
- [ ] B. volunteer to set up an equally big habitat
- [ ] C. offer to support the WAFWA monitoring job
- [ ] D. promise to raise funds for USFWS operations

<details>
<summary>✅ 点击查看答案与解析</summary>

**答案：B**
**解析：** 细节题。第三段提到，只要签署了恢复栖息地的计划，就不会被起诉。计划要求 "replace every acre destroyed with 2 new acres"，即自愿建立同等或更大的栖息地，对应 [B]。
</details>

**29. According to Ashe, the leading role in managing the species is _______.**
- [ ] A. the federal government
- [ ] B. the wildlife agencies
- [ ] C. the landowners
- [ ] D. the states

<details>
<summary>✅ 点击查看答案与解析</summary>

**答案：D**
**解析：** 细节题。第三段末尾 Ashe 说让 "states remain in the driver's seat"（各州处于驾驶座/主导地位），故选 [D] the states。
</details>

**30. Jay Lininger would most likely support _______.**
- [ ] A. industry groups
- [ ] B. the win-win rhetoric
- [ ] C. environmental groups
- [ ] D. the plan under challenge

<details>
<summary>✅ 点击查看答案与解析</summary>

