## Section IV: Writing (写作)

### Part A: Small Notice (小作文)

**47. Directions:** Suppose you won a translation contest and your friend, Jack, wrote an email to congratulate you and ask for advice on translation. Write him a reply to 1) thank him, and 2) give your advice.

**范文示例:**
> Dear Jack,
>
> Thank you so much for your congratulatory email regarding my win in the translation contest. I am truly delighted to share this joy with you.
>
> Regarding your inquiry about translation skills, here are a few suggestions. Firstly, always analyze the sentence structure thoroughly to grasp the underlying meaning before translating. Secondly, focus on finding appropriate words in the target language that convey the original tone accurately. Lastly, revise your draft at least three times to eliminate errors and polish the flow.
>
> I hope these tips are helpful. Let's catch up soon!
>
> Yours sincerely,
> Li Ming

### Part B: Essay based on Chart (大作文)

**48. Directions:** Write an essay based on the chart below. (Chart description: A pie chart showing college students' purposes of traveling: 37% for beautiful scenery, 35% for relieving pressure, etc.)

**范文示例:**
> The pie chart clearly illustrates the results of a survey concerning college students' purposes of traveling. Specifically, 37% of students travel to enjoy beautiful scenery, while 35% aim to relieve pressure from their studies.
>
> Several factors contribute to this trend. Primarily, fierce competition in modern society places immense pressure on college students, making travel an effective outlet for relaxation. Additionally, the improvement in living standards has made traveling more affordable for students, allowing them to explore the world and broaden their horizons.
>
> In my view, traveling is highly beneficial for young people. It not only alleviates stress but also enriches life experiences. Therefore, provided that time and finances permit, college students should seize opportunities to travel and see the outside world.
